Implement dequeue mutex lock (ref. issue #1)

It would be a shame to leave behind this excellent project so I tried to fix issue #1 by implementing a mutex lock on dequeuing, so that no consumer could receive a pending task more than once (which was happening wiithout that). I tested that in my own application, and that measure seems to solve the problem.

Update 0001_initial.py to add ordering meta options to HueySchedule and HueyTask models

Adding ordering options to HueySchedule and HueyTask models according to its Meta configuration to prevent Django from showing the following alert upon running "manage.py migrate":
    Your models in app(s): 'huey_django_orm' have changes that are not yet reflected in a migration, and so won't be applied.
    Run 'manage.py makemigrations' to make new migrations, and then re-run 'manage.py migrate' to apply them.
